> Alain, could you please take a look at this.

> 
> } catch (MIException e) {
>         // Do not throw anything in this case.
> 	throw new CDIException(e.getMessage());

For x number of reasons, GDB may not be able to get the Threads
call stack so it fails. The comment
"Do not throw anything ..."

Was because the old CDT UI could not handle errors thrown at it.
For example this can happen a lot on Solaris because of the
mix of LWP thread and kernel threads.

But now, the CDT UI should be handle this and not show stacks 
or threads if something went wrong.

The other log trace the NPE, I think you've already fix.
